The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Friday, August 29, 2003  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 The Indian Football Association kept open the option of a play-off final to decide the Super Division champions, this year. A meeting on Thursday, however, decided to scratch the system from next year. 				 																																																	Most of the members argued in favour of retaining the play-off final this year since the clubs participating had not been informed earlier about its abolishment.  Bowling meet				 																																																	 Wockhardt Medical B and Prudential ICICI won their matches against Tata Telecom C and Cognizant Technology C, respectively, in the Merchants Cup bowling meet at Nicco Super Bowl on Thursday. In other matches, Golden Steel beat BNK e-Solutions-B while Computech International defeated Bayview Technology-B. 				 																																																	 Over 450 took part in the state yoga championships held at Bijaygarh last week. Of them, 48  top three finishers in 16 age groups  have qualified for the national yoga meet, to be held in Jabalpur next month. 				 																																																	CHESS: The Telegraph Schools meet at Gorky Sadan from 3.30 pm. 				 																																																	FOOTBALL: CFL first division group A: Peerless SC vs Police AC (Mohun Bagan, 3.15 pm). Third division: championship play-off (quarter finals) Town Club vs Jugashanti SC (BG Press); Taltala ES vs YMSA (High Court). Relegation play-off (1st leg)  SAI (East Zone) vs Uttarpara SC (YMCA). Matches at 3 pm, unless otherwise mentioned. 				 																																																	SQUASH: East India junior open: Semi-finals at Calcutta Racket Club. 				 																																																	BOWLING: Merchants Cup at Nicco Super Bowl from 6 pm.				 																																																	BADMINTON: State meet at SAI. 				 																																																	GENERAL: National Sports Day celebration by BHA at Khudiram Anushilan Kendra from 3 pm. 				 																																																	WATERPOLO: Dr. Sarkar Allen meet at Vidyasagar Ydyan (YMCA) from 3.30 pm. 
